cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper discusses the use of deep learning for Magnetic Resonance Fingerprinting (MRF) reconstruction, which involves image processing and analysis. This falls under the scope of computer vision and pattern recognition.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes an accelerated iterative reconstruction method using a deep learning network, which involves machine learning techniques.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of convex regularization to jointly promote spatio-temporal regularities of the MRF time-series, which involves information theory concepts.
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper proposes a dictionary-free parameter estimation pipeline, which involves numerical analysis techniques.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the reconstruction of Magnetic Resonance Fingerprinting (MRF) images, which can be considered as a form of multimedia data.
